{
  "texts": [
    "In two usability and timing pretests (55 respondents, done in February 2022), the slider format emerged as user-friendly and intuitive, with no critical feedback.",
    "We directly asked respondents in the occupational prestige study: 'For each listed occupation below, please use the slider to indicate how you would rate the prestige of the occupation on a scale of 0 (the lowest level of prestige) to 100 (the highest level of prestige).'",
    "Analogical wording was used for the study of social value.",
    "We did not explain the concepts of prestige and social value, in order not to prime respondents.",
    "All respondents were asked to assess the 134 core titles (130 occupation titles and the four non-occupational roles), as well as 111 or 112 additional occupational titles equally distributed across the ISCO-08 groups (i.e., each respondent evaluated 245 or 246 occupation titles in total)."
  ]
}